---
title: Bell Pepper and Black Bean Quesadillas with an Arugula and Heirloom Tomato Salad
description: Well, you can mash some beans and you can give them a cheesy twist. But we’re telling you: you ain’t never had quesadillas quite like this. They’re stuffed with bell pepper and seasoned in a way that’s garlicky and bold—basically all the wholesome goodness you can fit in a tortilla fold. Add a zingy lime- and honey-dressed salad on the side and this meal is guaranteed to take you for a thrilling ride.
